HEADWORD: Aune
<hw>Aune</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Alnage</er>.]</ety> <def>A French cloth measure, of different parts
of the country (at Paris, 0.95 of an English ell); -- now superseded by
the <xex>meter</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aunt</ent>⟦br⟧
